.SH "NAME"
XISetClientPointer, XIGetClientPointa \- set or git tha ClientPointa device\&.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
#include <X11/extensions/XInput2\&.h>
.fi
.sp
.nf
XISetClientPointer( Display *display,
                    Window win,
                    int deviceid);
.fi
.sp
.nf
Bool XIGetClientPointer( Display *display,
                         Window win,
                         int *device);
.fi
.sp
.nf
display
       Specifies tha connection ta tha X server\&.
.fi
.sp
.nf
win
       Specifies a window belongin ta tha client\&. May be None\&.
.fi
.sp
.nf
deviceid
       Specifies tha ClientPointa device\&.
.fi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
Da ClientPointa is tha thang dat is percieved ta be the
core pointa fo' non\-XI protocol requests n' replies\&. Each
time a protocol message needz device\-dependent data n' the
device aint explicitly given, tha ClientPointa thang is
used ta obtain tha data\&. For example, a XQueryPointa request
will return tha coordinatez of tha ClientPointer\&.
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
XISetClientPointa request sets tha ClientPointa thang for
the client dat owns tha given window\&. If win is None, the
requestin client\*(Aqs ClientPointa is set ta tha device
specified wit deviceid\&. Only masta pointa devices can be set
as ClientPointer\&.
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
XISetClientPointa n' can generate a BadDevice n' a BadWindow
error\&.
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
Da XIGetClientPointa request returns tha ClientPointer\*(Aqs
device ID fo' tha client dat owns tha given window\&. If win is
None, tha requestin client\*(Aqs ClientPointa is returned\&.
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
win may be a cold-ass lil client ID instead of a window\&.
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
XIGetClientPointa can generate a BadWindow error\&.
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
